          <h1>Ed Waller</h1>
          <br>
          <br>
          <p align="justify"><font face="Georgia, Times New Roman, Times, serif">I
              am a full Professor at the University of Ontario Institute of
              Technology (UOIT), in the Faculty of Energy Systems and Nuclear
              Science, Oshawa, Ontario, Canada and am currently an <a href="http://www.nserc-crsng.gc.ca/">NSERC</a>/<a
                href="http://www.unene.ca/">UNENE</a> Industrial Research Chair
              in Health Physics and Environmental Safety, collaborating with the
              Senior Chair holder, <a href="http://nuclear.uoit.ca/#%21waker">Dr.
                Anthony Waker</a>.</font></p>
          <p> <font face="Georgia, Times New Roman, Times, serif">I earned my
              BSc in Physics (Hons) and MScE in Chemical Engineering at the <a
                href="http://www.unb.ca/">University of New Brunswick</a> (UNB),
              Fredericton, New Brunswick and my PhD in Nuclear Engineering and
              Science at <a href="http://www.rpi.edu/">Rensselaer Polytechnic
                Institute</a>, New York (RPI). &nbsp;I worked for over 15 years
              in industry for <a href="http://www.saic.com/canada/">Science
                Applications International Corporation</a>, primarily in threat
              assessment, health physics and appl</font><font face="Georgia, Times New Roman, Times, serif">ications
              of radiation. &nbsp;In 2003 I joined the University of Ontario
              Institute of Technology.&nbsp; </font> </p>
          <p align="justify"><font face="Georgia, Times New Roman, Times, serif">I
              hold a number of certifications, such as Professional Engineer,
              Ontario (<a href="http://www.peo.on.ca/">PEng</a>), Certified
              Associate Industrial Hygienist (<a href="http://www.abih.org/">CAIH</a>)
              and Certified Health Physicist (<a href="http://www.hps1.org/aahp/">CHP</a>).
              I teach a variety of courses including radiation protection,
              health physics, environmental effects of radiation, environmental
              modeling, Monte Carlo methods and nuclear forensics at UOIT. My
              research is in areas of emergency response, radiation dosimetry
              (internal and external), applied health physics, radiation safety,
              counter-terrorism and threat assessment. &nbsp;</font></p>
          <p> </p>
          <p align="justify"><font face="Georgia, Times New Roman, Times, serif">I
              hold a private pilot license (not actively flying), and I actively
              scuba dive. My preferred sport is <a href="http://www.rugbycanada.ca/">rugby</a>
              (not so much to play anymore but certainly to watch) and I have
              been known to play in the odd soccer game once in a while. </font></p>
          <p> </p>
          <p align="justify"><font face="Georgia, Times New Roman, Times, serif">My
              email address is <a href="mailto:ed.waller@uoit.ca">ed.waller@uoit.ca</a>
            </font></p>
